{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addOption"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"GLibOptionGroupT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"group"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GLibOptionGroupT"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GLibOptionGroupT"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"OptionGroupProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib19OptionGroupProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is comparable to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_option_context_add_group()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_application_add_main_option_entries()"},{"type":"text","text":", this function does"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not deal with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"type":"text","text":" and never transmits options to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"primary instance."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The reason for that is because, by the time the options arrive at the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"primary instance, it is typically too late to do anything with them."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Taking the GTK option group as an example: GTK will already have been"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initialised by the time the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication::command-line"},{"type":"text","text":" handler runs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In the case that this is not the first-running instance of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application, the existing instance may already have been running for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a very long time."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This means that the options from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" are only really usable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the case that the instance of the application being run is the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"first instance.  Passing options like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--display="},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--gdk-debug="},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on future runs will have no effect on the existing primary instance."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calling this function will cause the options in the supplied option"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group to be parsed, but it does not cause you to be “opted in” to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"new functionality whereby unrecognised options are rejected even if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_APPLICATION_HANDLES_COMMAND_LINE"},{"type":"text","text":" was given."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/applicationref\/addoption(group:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/addOption(group:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" to the commandline handling of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"application"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"addOption(group:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addOption"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"GLibOptionGroupT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"group"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GLibOptionGroupT"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO19ApplicationProtocolPAAE9addOption5groupyqd___t4GLib0e5GroupC0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO14ApplicationRefV","extendedModule":"GIO","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/ApplicationProtocol-Implementations"]]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationRef/addOption(group:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"addOption(group:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addOption"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"GLibOptionGroupT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"group"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GLibOptionGroupT"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" to the commandline handling of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"application"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/addOption(group:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationref\/addoption(group:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"role":"collection","title":"GIO","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationRef/ApplicationProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"ApplicationProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/ApplicationProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationref\/applicationprotocol-implementations"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationRef":{"role":"symbol","title":"ApplicationRef","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ApplicationRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" is the foundation of an application.  It wraps some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"low-level platform-specific services and is intended to act as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"foundation for higher-level application classes such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MxApplication"},{"type":"text","text":".  In general, you should not use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this class outside of a higher level framework."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ApplicationRef"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationref"}}}